headline: Proposed ACA Subsidy Changes Could Be a Game Changer for Centene (CNC)
summary: Centene Corporation recently faced market pressure after President Donald Trump called for redirecting ACA healthcare subsidies directly to individuals instead of insurance companies, a proposal gaining traction in the U.S. Senate and raising uncertainty about federal funding for government-sponsored insurers. This development highlights significant risk to Centene’s core business model, which relies heavily on stable federal funding flowing through insurance providers to support Medicaid,...

headline: More than 500 Unhoused Angelenos to find Housing and Get Medical, Behavioral Health and other Services thanks to $2 Million Investment by Health Net in LA Family Housing
summary: Health Net, one of California's most experienced Medi-Cal managed care health plans and company of Centene Corporation (NYSE: CNC), awarded a renewal of a $1 million grant to LA Family Housing (LAFH). This marks the second consecutive year of this significant partnership, which directly supports LAFH's innovative Housing Location program and accelerates efforts to secure permanent affordable housing for individuals experiencing homelessness in Los Angeles County's Service Planning Area (SPA) 2.
